28
00:01:10,680 --> 00:01:14,300
that terrible Chinese movie Operation Red
Sea.

29
00:01:14,300 --> 00:01:15,500
With the announcement,

30
00:01:15,510 --> 00:01:21,900
the US Trade Representative published a long
list of 1,102 products

31
00:01:21,900 --> 00:01:25,420
that will be hit with tariffs starting July
6.

32
00:01:25,420 --> 00:01:28,700
That list includes stuff we all use every
day,

33
00:01:28,700 --> 00:01:33,470
like can-sealing machines, centrifuges and
Klystron tubes?

34
00:01:33,470 --> 00:01:36,440
Wait, what’s that Shelley?

35
00:01:36,440 --> 00:01:39,140
The tariffs don’t include consumer goods,

36
00:01:39,140 --> 00:01:40,530
like mobile phones and TVs?

37
00:01:40,530 --> 00:01:43,140
Well, that’s great news.

38
00:01:43,140 --> 00:01:45,780
Looks like American consumers will still be
able to enjoy

39
00:01:45,780 --> 00:01:48,979
Wal-Mart’s everyday low prices.

40
00:01:48,979 --> 00:01:53,820
And Wal-Mart’s everyday low standards for
Chinese suppliers.

41
00:01:53,820 --> 00:01:56,950
But just because the new tariffs don’t cover
consumer goods

42
00:01:56,950 --> 00:02:01,340
doesn’t mean they’re not a big deal for
both countries.

43
00:02:01,340 --> 00:02:04,640
Most of the goods on the tariff list are related
to China’s

44
00:02:04,640 --> 00:02:08,489
Made in China 2025 strategic plan to dominate

45
00:02:08,489 --> 00:02:13,659
hi-tech industries like robotics, aerospace,
and industrial machinery.

46
00:02:13,659 --> 00:02:17,120
The Made in China 2025 plan is designed to
drive

47
00:02:17,120 --> 00:02:19,780
future economic growth for China,

48
00:02:19,780 --> 00:02:23,459
in large measure at the expense of the US.

49
00:02:23,459 --> 00:02:25,849
And a lot of these products were made after
China

50
00:02:25,849 --> 00:02:28,760
stole American technology.

51
00:02:28,760 --> 00:02:32,819
In some cases, the Chinese military simply
hacked in,

52
00:02:32,819 --> 00:02:36,090
stole it, and gave it to local Chinese firms.

53
00:02:36,090 --> 00:02:37,129
In other cases,

54
00:02:37,129 --> 00:02:40,450
it was because of a Chinese law that US companies

55
00:02:40,450 --> 00:02:42,840
doing business in China were required to

56
00:02:42,840 --> 00:02:45,870
set up joint ventures with Chinese firms

57
00:02:45,870 --> 00:02:48,780
and then hand over their intellectual property.

58
00:02:48,780 --> 00:02:51,659
That’s why when announcing the tariffs,

59
00:02:51,659 --> 00:02:54,450
Trump said the the US “can no longer tolerate

60
00:02:54,450 --> 00:02:57,799
losing our technology and intellectual property

61
00:02:57,799 --> 00:03:00,739
through unfair economic practices.”

62
00:03:00,739 --> 00:03:03,260
One thing Trump hopes to achieve with the
tariffs

63
00:03:03,260 --> 00:03:07,829
is to force China to change parts of its state-led
economic system

64
00:03:07,829 --> 00:03:11,029
that put foreign companies at a disadvantage.

65
00:03:11,029 --> 00:03:13,909
But with Friday’s publication of the tariff
list,

66
00:03:13,909 --> 00:03:17,040
Chinese state media got seriously triggered.

67
00:03:17,040 --> 00:03:20,849
An editorial in the Communist Party’s official
People's Daily

68
00:03:20,849 --> 00:03:23,730
said the US was instigating a trade war

69
00:03:23,730 --> 00:03:27,230
and that it would be “extremely destructive
to global trade,

70
00:03:27,230 --> 00:03:30,669
economic globalization, multilateral trade
systems

71
00:03:30,669 --> 00:03:34,049
and global production supply chains.”

72
00:03:34,049 --> 00:03:35,280
State-run Xinhua News said,

73
00:03:35,280 --> 00:03:37,700
“The wise man builds bridges,

74
00:03:37,700 --> 00:03:39,099
the fool builds walls.”

75
00:03:39,099 --> 00:03:47,730
Anyway, state-run CCTV announced that China
would fight back.

76
00:03:47,730 --> 00:03:51,040
“China has no choice but to fight back strongly

77
00:03:51,040 --> 00:03:53,809
to resolutely protect its national interests

78
00:03:53,809 --> 00:03:56,079
and the people's interests,

79
00:03:56,079 --> 00:03:58,249
and to resolutely defend globalization

80
00:03:58,249 --> 00:04:01,159
and the multilateral trading system.

81
00:04:01,159 --> 00:04:03,150
We will immediately publish levies

82
00:04:03,150 --> 00:04:06,069
of the same scale and same strength.”

83
00:04:06,069 --> 00:04:07,269
And they did.

84
00:04:07,269 --> 00:04:09,609
China announced essentially tit-for-tat tariffs,

85
00:04:09,609 --> 00:04:12,019
also worth $50 billion dollars.

86
00:04:12,019 --> 00:04:15,950
Some of which are also going into effect starting
July 6.

87
00:04:15,950 --> 00:04:18,739
China’s tariff list on US goods includes

88
00:04:18,739 --> 00:04:21,489
soybeans, beef, and whiskey.

89
00:04:21,489 --> 00:04:24,020
There goes my plan for opening a tofu steakhouse-

90
00:04:24,020 --> 00:04:27,300
slash-whiskey bar in downtown Beijing.

91
00:04:27,300 --> 00:04:30,460
But is a trade war really going to be destructive

92
00:04:30,460 --> 00:04:32,760
as China is making it out to be?

93
00:04:33,180 --> 00:04:36,000
Well, probably not for the US.

94
00:04:36,000 --> 00:04:37,909
Experts say economic growth in US

95
00:04:37,909 --> 00:04:40,550
won’t be affected all that much.

96
00:04:40,550 --> 00:04:44,310
Rich Sega, global chief investment strategist
at Conning,

97
00:04:44,310 --> 00:04:47,060
says Chinese tariffs won’t be “enough
to derail

98
00:04:47,060 --> 00:04:50,220
strong growth in the US because lower taxes

99
00:04:50,220 --> 00:04:53,560
and deregulation outweigh trade.”

100
00:04:53,560 --> 00:04:54,569
As for China,

101
00:04:54,569 --> 00:04:59,289
this could be a big hit to their Made in China
2025 plan.

102
00:04:59,289 --> 00:05:01,190
And that doesn’t even include the additional

103
00:05:01,190 --> 00:05:05,050
